LAGOS (SundiataPost) – Lagos has continued to remain the epicentre of COVID-19 in Nigeria, accounting for 209 out of 452 new cases confirmed on Tuesday. Oyo State came a distant second with 67 new cases. With the new cases confirmed on Tuesday, Nigeria now has 21,371 confirmed cases of COVID-19. Out of this number, Lagos has 9,037 cases, followed by the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) with 1,605 while Kano has 1,190. In addition, death toll from the pandemic now stands at 533 according to the update released by the NCDC late on Tuesday night. The full report is as follows: 452 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-209Oyo-67Delta-37Ogun-36FCT-22Abia-20Enugu-16Bauchi-15Kaduna-8Ondo-8Osun-7Imo-3Benue-3Borno-1 21,371 confirmed7,338 discharged533 deaths See the state by state breakdown: ABUJA - In what is gradually creating panic in Nigeria the Coronavirus pandemic has increased alarmingly to 407 confirmed cases, the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) reported late on Wednesday. The NCDC reported 34 new cases, the highest in a single day since Nigeria's index case in February.Lagos remains… April 15, 2020 In "News" ABUJA (SundiataPost) - Nigeria on Wednesday crossed the 11,000 mark in the record of COVID-19 cases. The country now has 11,166 confirmed cases of coronavirus. The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) released the new figure in its latest update on Wednesday night.In addition it reported 348 new cases out… June 4, 2020 In "Top Stories" two cases of the novel coronavirus in Kogi State. Nigeria on Tuesday recorded 389 new cases of Coronavirus (COVID-19) This sums the total number of confirmed cases in Nigeria to 8733. According to the data from the Nigeria Center for Disease Control, NCDC, there are now 35 States, excluding Cross… May 28, 2020 In "News"